# Force browsers to re-validate every page load so a new deploy's hashed
# asset URLs (in the rebuilt index.html) get picked up immediately. Without
# this, a cached old index.html keeps pointing at /assets/*.css chunks that
# no longer exist, and the SPA fallback in _redirects answers those stale
# asset requests with index.html — the browser then rejects HTML served as
# CSS/JS with "MIME type ('text/html') is not a supported stylesheet".
#
# Cloudflare Pages applies the most specific matching block, so the
# /assets/* override below lets hashed chunks stay long-cached.

/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
